The paragraph:
The U.S. Federal Aviation Administration (FAA) on Tuesday proposed a rule that would require all airplanes and helicopters in the United States to have a digital license plate, a move aimed at improving safety and reducing the risk of accidents. The FAA said the proposed rule would require aircraft owners to install a digital license plate on their aircraft by Dec. 31, 2024. The digital license plate would be a small, lightweight device that would be attached to the aircraft and would display the aircraft's registration number, owner's name, and other information. The FAA said the digital license plate would help improve safety by making it easier for air traffic controllers and other pilots to identify aircraft and avoid collisions. The proposed rule is open for public comment until March 15. (Reporting by David Shepardson; Editing by Leslie Adler)
